o lived by a stretch of water, Middle English and Low German <i>water</i>."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Waterman was born about 1470. He had at least 1 daughter with Unknown. He died in Odiham, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1470–":"umbes 1470–Surnud","1470–1558":"1470–1558","1494–1556":"1494–1556","1470–Male":"1470–Surnud","1558":"1558","about 1470":"umbes 1470","1556":"1556","1494":"1494","1470":"1470","about 1494":"umbes 1494","Andover, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom":"Andover, Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Odiham, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom":"Odiham, Hampshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1470–":"noin 1470–Kuollut","1470–1558":"1470–1558","1494–1556":"1494–1556","1470–Male":"1470–Kuollut","1558":"1558","about 1470":"noin 1470","1556":"1556","1494":"1494","1470":"1470","about 1494":"noin 1494","Andover, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom":"Andover, Hampshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Odiham, Hampshire, England, United Kingdom":"Odiham, Hampshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1470–":"environ 1470–Décédé","1470–1558":"1470–1558","1494–1556":"1494–1556","1470–Male":"1470–Décédé","1558":"1558","about 1470":"environ 1470","155